cs.CG, cs.GR, cs.DS, cs.NA, cs.CV. 

The paper deals with optimization algorithms for Moebius transformations, which are commonly used in computational geometry and computer graphics. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.GR (Computer Graphics) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions applications in vertex separation and symmetry display (cs.DS - Data Structures and Algorithms), viewpoint selection (cs.NA - Numerical Analysis), and brain flat mapping (cs.CV - Computer Vision), which further support these sub-categories.
